The paper describes the development of an unmanned mobile manipulator robot that is able to navigate, recognize and manipulate objects. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of computer vision algorithms for object recognition (cs.CV) and the use of artificial intelligence techniques for autonomous operation (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of sensor feedback for control and decision-making (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the robot and the classification and recognition algorithms, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
